node.text: Have you ever visited Msida in Malta? Msida is an old fishing town with a famous marina (image credit: @allardschager)
We hope you had a wonderful Christmas Day. Our ideal Boxing Day is a stroll along Golden Bay Beach. How will you be spending the day? (image credit: @ingmarov)
Wishing you and yours a very Merry Christmas! (image credit: @justine.previ.photography
It's almost Christmas! How will you be spending Christmas Eve? If you're in Malta, wander the streets of Valletta and take in the festive scenery. (image credit: @anya_kengu.ru)
Worth the climb for this stunning sunset over Ramla Bay (image credit: @rhysjsimmons)
An incredible shot of Naxxar, a town in Northern Malta showcasing the incredible Naxxar Church dedicated to Our Lady of Victories (image credit: @intl.fritzphotography)
Some of the most beautiful doors in Malta! This gorgeous Bougainvillea can be found in Mdina (image credit: @restlessworker)
A stunning sunset over the village of Bahar Ic-Caghaq in Malta (image credit: @mark.muscat.photo)
The historic gates to the city of Mdina are iconic. The city and the gates have been used in multiple films and TV series including @gameofthrones (image credit: @zuzanacloud)
The Maltese Archipelago is full of hidden gems to explore (image credit: james.scic)
Tag the person that you would want to wander through quiet streets of Mdina with, known as the Silent City (image credit: @votan_meister)

In just over a month the @vallettabaroquefestival will return to the city for its 8th year. Enjoy two weeks of outstanding musical talent in beautiful locations across the city, including the stunning interior of St. John's Co-Cathedral (image credit: @ponpon.e)
Malta's rugged coastlines are just waiting for you to explore them. Just a three-hour flight from the UK, what are you waiting for - book now! (image credit: @jos_awad)

Today is Republic Day in Malta. The annual day of remembrance began in 1974, when Malta no longer called Queen Elizabeth their Head of State and instead elected a President as a republic (image credit: @iamsean_b)
Dramatic skies over the medieval city of Mdina (image credit: @shanafenech)
It always feels like summer in Malta, especially along the palm tree lined boardwalk in Qawra (Image credit: @svetlana_agius)

Feeling festive yet? Malta's Christmas season is in full swing with an abundance of Christmas markets, beautifully decorated churches and glittering lights throughout the city of Valletta (image credit: @jasamineazzopardi)
What's your favourite thing about Malta? We love the fact that the island is full of history (image credit: iamchrisborg)
A beautiful sunset stroll through St Julian's is the perfect way to spend a Sunday. What's your ideal Sunday activity? Comment below (image credit: @jelenapa)
Breathtaking sunsets from the clifftops of the Maltese Archipelago (image credit: @tanguygeradon)
Jump for joy - it's Friday! You can have views for days on top of this gorgeous Wied il-Mielaħ window in Gozo (image credit: @studio.impala)
The Lower Barrakka Gardens are a beautiful oasis in the middle of Malta's vibrant capital city, Valletta (image credit: @feastoftravel)
The streets of Malta are lined with brightly coloured balconies. Comment on your favourite colourful spot in Malta below (image credit: @malta_me_please)
Who wants to take a selfie at Tritons' Fountain in Valletta? It's the perfect Instagrammable spot! (image credit: @ntcandrejphoto)
